description.narrative: As in 2020, Senegal demonstrated resilience particularly in the areas of health, nutrition, HIV and WASH.; UNICEF continued its support to ensure the continuity of basic health services in compliance with barriers measures. The major event was the launch of the Covid-19 immunization. The supplementary immunization activities allowed for the integration of other interventions such as vitamin A supplementation, deworming, girls immunization against Human Papilloma Virus (HPV), and other routine vaccines. The support to the nutrition program was focused on the capacity building of key actors and the availability of essential supplies at operational level. | Status:Met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
